After failing to get Justice Raymond Zondo to recuse himself, former president Jacob Zuma left the commission without permission. AFP/Guillem Sartorio JOHANNESBURG - The Jacob Zuma Foundation has applauded the former president for walking away from the Zondo Commission. It says he insists he'd rather face jail than allow himself to be bullied. READ:Â Zondo: Zuma walking out of state capture inquiry 'a serious matter' The foundation's labelled the state capture inquiry a comedy of errors. It says it's concerned that chairperson Raymond Zondo was the arbiter in his own dispute and it accuses evidence leaders of plotting against Zuma. After failing to get Zondo to recuse himself, Zuma left the commission without permission.